		<li>Completed registration application (see below)
			<ul>
				<li>For medical, academic, research, and veterinary uses, <a title="Registration Application for Users of Radiation Machines in Healing Arts, Veterinary Medicine and Academic Facilities, RC 226-2" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&amp;ItemID=19923">Registration Application for Users of Radiation Machines in Healing Arts, Veterinary Medicine and Academic Facilities, RC 226-2</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 27KB)</span></li>
				<li>For industrial uses, <a title="Registration Application for Industrial Radiation Machines, RC 226-3" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&amp;ItemID=8589965283">Registration Application for Industrial Radiation Machines, RC 226-3</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 32KB)</span></li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Completed Notice of Intent to Work in Texas under Reciprocity form (see below)
			<ul>
				<li>For industrial radiography - <a title="Notice of Intent to Work in Texas Under Reciprocity, RC 252-3" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&amp;ItemID=8589990149">Notice of Intent to Work in Texas Under Reciprocity, RC 252-3</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 27KB)</span></li>
				<li>For all others - <a title="Notice of Intent to Work in Texas Under Reciprocity - Non Industrial Radiography" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&amp;ItemID=8590002915">Notice of Intent to Work in Texas Under Reciprocity - Non Industrial-Radiography</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 106KB)</span></li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Completed qualification forms (RC Forms 255-E, 255-T and/or 255- OS) for each radiographer who will be working in Texas if the reciprocity request is for industrial radiography (IR/NDT) or RSO qualifications (RC 42-3) if non-IR reciprocity;
			<ul>
				<li><a title="Trainee Qualification Form, RC 255-E" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&ItemID=8589982187">Trainee Qualification Form, RC 255-E</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 27KB)</span></li>
				<li><a title="Trainer Qualification, RC 255-T" href="https://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&ItemID=8589982190">Trainer Qualification, RC 255-T</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 65KB)</span></li>
				<li><a title="Radiographer Qualification - OJT Years" href="https://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&ItemID=8589982185">Radiographer Qualification (OJT Years), RC 255-OS</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 35KB)</span></li>
				<li><a title="Radiation Safety Officer (RSO) Qualification Form, RC 42-3" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&amp;ItemID=19926">Radiation Safety Officer (RSO) Qualification Form, RC 42-3</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 301KB)</span><br/><strong>NOTE</strong>: RSO qualification form RC 42-3 may be used for medical reciprocity only</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Name and Texas licensing board number of the practitioner if the machines are used on humans;</li>
		<li>Copy of the applicant’s current certificate of registration or equivalent document;</li>
		<li>Copy of the applicant’s current operating and safety procedures pertinent to the proposed use;</li>
		<li>Fee as specified in <a title="Title 25 Texas Administrative Code, §289.204(d)" href="http://texreg.sos.state.tx.us/public/readtac$ext.TacPage?sl=R&app=9&p_dir=&p_rloc=&p_tloc=&p_ploc=&pg=1&p_tac=&ti=25&pt=1&ch=289&rl=204">Title 25 Texas Administrative Code, §289.204(d)</a>; and</li>
		<li>Qualifications of personnel who will be operating human use x-ray machines.</li>
	</ol>
	
