	<p>Once reciprocity is granted, the out of state registrant shall submit the appropriate form below at least 3 days prior to each entry into the state:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>For industrial radiography - <a title="Notice of Intent to Work in Texas Under Reciprocity, RC 252-3" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&amp;ItemID=8589990149">Notice of Intent to Work in Texas Under Reciprocity, RC 252-3</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 27KB)</span></li>
		<li>For all others - <a title="Notice of Intent to Work in Texas Under Reciprocity - Non Industrial Radiography" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/WorkArea/linkit.aspx?LinkIdentifier=id&amp;ItemID=8590002915">Notice of Intent to Work in Texas Under Reciprocity - Non Industrial-Radiography</a> <span class="small">(PDF, 106KB)</span></li>
	</ul>
	<p>If the 3 day period will impose an undue hardship, the out-of-state registrant may obtain permission to proceed sooner.</p>
	<p>If operating <strong><em>industrial radiography</em></strong>, submit your notice to Patricia Mackey by fax at (512) 834-6654. For assistance, call (512) 834-6770 ext. 2000.</p>
	<p>If operating <strong><em>human use, minimal threat or other industrial machines</em></strong>, submit your notice by email to <a title="tinesha.durr@dshs.state.tx.us" href="mailto:tinesha.durr@dshs.state.tx.us">Tinesha Durr</a>, or fax to (512) 834-6622. For assistance, call (512) 834-6770 x2812.</p>
	<p>If you have reciprocity registration questions, contact <a title="karen.verser@dshs.state.tx.us" href="mailto:karen.verser@dshs.state.tx.us">Karen Verser</a> by email, or by phone at (512) 834-6688 ext. 2233.</p>
	
